<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN261-intro">
      <p type="edition">tiṇai – karantai; tuṟai – cerumalaital<gap quantity="4" reason="lost" unit="character"/>āvūr mūlaṅkiḻār pāṭiyatu.
      </p>
      <p xml:lang="en" type="translation">  
      </p>
    </div>
    <div xml:id="PN261">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>antō ventai yaṭaiyāp pēril</l>
<l>vaṇṭupaṭu naṟaviṟ ṟaṇṭā maṇṭaiyoṭu</l>
<l>varaiyāp peruñcōṟṟu murivāy muṟṟam</l>
<l>veṟṟiyāṟ ṟampiyi ṉeṟṟaṟ ṟākak</l>
<l>kaṇṭaṉeṉ maṉṟa cōrkaveṉ kaṇṇē</l>
<l>vaiyaṅ kāvalar vaḷaṅkeḻu tirunakar</l>
<l>maiyal yāṉai yayāvuyirt taṉṉa</l>
<l>neyyulai corinta maiyū ṉōcai</l>
<l>putukkaṇ mākkaḷ cetukka ṇārap</l>
<l>payantaṉai maṉṉāṉ muṉṉē yiṉiyē</l>
<l>pallā taḻīiya kallā valvi</l>
<l>luḻaikuraṟ kūkai yaḻaippa vāṭṭi</l>
<l>nākumulai yaṉṉa naṟumpūṅ karantai</l>
<l>virakaṟi yāḷar marapiṟ cūṭṭa</l>
<l>niraiyivaṭ ṭantu naṭuka lākiya</l>
<l>veṉvēl viṭalai yiṉmaiyiṟ pulampik</l>
<l>koymmaḻit talaiyoṭu kaimmaiyuṟak kalaṅkiya</l>
<l>kaḻikala makaṭūup pōlap</l>
<l>pulleṉ ṟaṉaiyāṟ pallaṇi yiḻantē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l corresp="1">  Alas! our father’s house that was not locked, </l>
<l corresp="3">the courtyard with a curved opening, with unlimited great rice </l>
<l corresp="2">along with undiminishing jars of toddy to which bees came, </l>
<l>I have seen become thus – like what? – </l>
<l corresp="4-5b">like a boat on an empty river. </l>
<l corresp="5cd">	Let my eyes tire. </l>
<l corresp="6">Fertile auspicious mansion of the world’s guardian, </l>
<l corresp="10a-c">before you did yield, </l>
<l corresp="9">for the lack-lustre eyes of new-eyed people to become full, </l>
<l corresp="8">the sound of goat meat poured on the oily hearth, </l>
<l corresp="7">like the langourous sigh of an rutting elephant. </l>
<l corresp="10d">	Now, </l>
<l corresp="18">like the women with ornaments put away </l>
<l corresp="17">who are upset to experience widowhood, with heads plucked [and] shaved, </l>
<l corresp="16">lamenting the absence of the warrior with victorious spear, </l>
<l>	who chased away the unlearned strong bows that embraced </l>
<l>	many cows, as owls with nearby voices shrieked, (11f.)</l>
<l corresp="14">	while putting on, according to the custom of men who know the means, </l>
<l corresp="13">	Karantai with fragrant flowers like female breasts, </l>
<l corresp="15">	brought the herds here [and] has become a hero stone, </l>
<l corresp="19">your have become empty, having lost many decorations. </l>
</lg>
